  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Housing Development Finance Corporation Limited (HDFC or the company) is one of India&apos;s premier financial institutions. The company was incorporated in 1977 with a share capital of Rs.100 million ($11 million) and has since grown to become the largest residential mortgage finance institution in the country, with over 50% of the total market share and a market capitalization of $1.9 billion equivalent.

The purpose of the project is to provide HDFC long-term funding not available in the local market and to assist the company in extending the maturity of syndicated funding accessible internationally.  Funds from the investment would be used by HDFC to extend its reach to the underserved middle and lower income segments of the population in India.</narrative>
  </description>
